sentences: Talal Maddah (5 August 1940 – 11 August 2000; Arabic: طلال مدَّاح) was a Saudi Arabian musician and composer.
During his career, he participated in many festivals in Saudi Arabia between 1960 and 2000.
In the 1960s, Talal Maddah became famous due to the birth of Saudi Arabia's official radio.
In 1976, he had his first pan-Arab hit with "Muqadir".
Moreover, throughout his 50-year career journey, Maddah composed more than 1000 songs.
In 1984, King Fahd of Saudi Arabia awarded Maddah the Order of Merit of the Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques for his work.
Talal Maddah was the subject of a Google Doodle on 5 August 2018, the 78th anniversary of his birth.
